This paper discusses the privacy risks associated with machine learning algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also examines the effect of overfitting and influence on privacy risk, which relates to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to infer attributes, which falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses formal and empirical analyses, which relates to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the connection between membership inference and attribute inference, which relates to the sub-category of computer systems and networking (cs.CY).
